President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has sent a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13536 with respect to Somalia will continue beyond April 12, 2022. The President believes that the situation in Somalia still poses an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. This action is taken in accordance with Section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act, which requires the President to publish a notice in the Federal Register and transmit it to Congress to continue a national emergency.